                    },
                    "created": "2010-02-05T01:16:46.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-02-05T01:16:46.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/40407",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=hcderaad",
                        "name": "hcderaad",
                        "displayName": "Hans de Raad",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I finally had some spare time left to dive into this problem, and as a result managed to solve it.\r\nOr, perhaps better, managed to find the flaws in my own assumptions about the inner workings of this very useful piece of code.\r\n\r\nWhat happens is as follows:\r\n\r\nWhen normally entering text in an autocomplete field, a query is performed on the value part of the entry (ie: <input type=text value=\"this part\">), but on loading the initial selectlike entry, this part is not used, instead, in your autocompletecontroller, you have to catch an \"id' GET variable and handle that in your db.\r\n\r\nNow this functionality works beautifully in my app.\r\n\r\nIf this could be clafiried in the docs, i for one would be very grateful.\r\n\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=hcderaad",
                        "name": "hcderaad",
                        "displayName": "Hans de Raad",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-05-07T07:53:14.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-05-07T07:53:14.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
